{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase Mileage allowance from 45p per mile to 75p per mile",
        "additional_details": "Employees that use their own car for business journeys can claim tax relief on the approved mileage rate. They can\u2019t claim separately for owning and running costs like fuel and MOTs, as the business mileage rate covers these expenditures. \r\n\r\nTherefore with the increase of running costs aforementioned due to inflation, it is time the 45p is increased in line with the ever-increasing costs. \r\n\r\nThis amount should also be reviewed periodically.",
        "background": "The Government should increase the tax-free approved Mileage Allowance Payment rate of 45p per mile for the first 10,000 miles for cars and vans. As advised, the 45p per mile was introduced 12 years ago and needs increasing",
